  &lt;p id="q9uKzR"&gt;&lt;a href="https://screeningroom.a24films.com/"&gt;A24’s &lt;em&gt;The Green Knight&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will make its virtual debut much earlier than expected — on August 18th, you’ll be able to buy a $20 ticket to stream the film through A24’s Screening Room platform. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="xx1qTD"&gt;The one-night-only stream isn’t a full streaming release for rental or purchase, given that &lt;em&gt;The Green Knight&lt;/em&gt; is still otherwise exclusive to theaters. (A regular digital release will come later on in the theatrical cycle.) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="HwbOvl"&gt;As such, the screening is also far more limited than a typical rental: once you’ve purchased a $20 ticket, you’ll be able to stream the film during a four-hour window on August 18th starting at 9PM ET. The stream does come with a bonus Q&amp;amp;A with the cast and crew after the film, however. &lt;/p&gt;
