  &lt;p id="3Luv5h"&gt;After weeks of negotiations, the Senate approved a bipartisan &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2021/8/2/22605917/senate-negotiators-bipartisan-infrastructure-broadband-electric-vehicles-cryptocurrency"&gt;$1 trillion infrastructure&lt;/a&gt; package Tuesday authorizing over $500 billion in new spending to improve roads, bridges, and other physical infrastructure like broadband and EV charging. It’s the largest domestic spending bill in over a decade. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="RQqDH8"&gt;“It’s taken quite a while. There have been a lot of bumps in the road,” Majority Leader Chuck Schumer (D-NY) said Tuesday. &lt;/p&gt;
